	<h2>Installing R</h2>
	<p>If you haven't already installed R, you can do so at the <a href="http://cran.r-project.org/">Comprehensive R Archive Network</a> (CRAN).</p>
	
	<h2>Basic Calculations</h2>
		<p>R can be used for any kind of basic calculation.</p>
		<blockquote>
			<font face = "Courier">
				> 3+3 <br>
				[1] 6<br>
				> 2*4<br>
				[1] 8<br>
				> (369-1)/6<br>
				[1] 61.33333
			</font>
		</blockquote>
		<p>The <font face = "Courier">></font> symbol is the prompt for input.  The output is preceded by <font face = "Courier">[1]</font> to
		indicate that it is the first element in a vector.</p>
		<p>Vectors are one of the basic data structures in R.  </p>
	
